def my_func(vector):
    # Convert the input string to a list of integers
    vector = list(map(int, vector.strip('[]').split()))
    
    # Find the minimum value in the list
    min_value = min(vector)
    
    # Return the index of the first occurrence of the minimum value
    return vector.index(min_value)

def my_func(input_str):
    # Parse the input string to extract the list and the target index
    input_str = input_str.strip('[]')
    parts = input_str.split(',')
    vector = list(map(int, parts[0].strip().split()))
    target_index = int(parts[1].strip())
    
    # Return the element at the target index
    return vector[target_index]
